<br />One is SDTV output. PCs with Intel graphics usually don't have it without a $40 VGA-to-composite adapter. Another is the ability to use it and your TV in separate rooms at the same time. So unless it's cheaper than an Acer Aspire Revo nettop and a scan converter...

		

