<br />The next thing is the price. I paid the $135 plus shipping. That is quite a
<br />lot of money. When I got the powerpak I found out it doesn't work....
<br />
<br />What do you do when something you ordered doesn't work ? Right, you
<br />mail to support. Unfortunately I didn't get any answers there. I ended up
<br />finding answers here in the nesdev forum. Surely the store website would
<br />be updated soon I thought. Strangely enough that never happened. After
<br />some time I realized that apparently I belong the unlucky percentage of
<br />people owning the "wrong" SNES version which isn't supported - I
<br />wonder if it is supported now, the website didn't say last time I checked.
